14 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
15 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
16 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 4019.1 of Title 69, unless there
17 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
18 A. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall require a
19 post-installation inspection for any storm pipe that does not pass a
20 structural dead load test prior to installation.
21 B. The post-installation inspection shall be conducted by a
22 qualified engineer or inspector approved by the Department to ensure
23 compliance with industry standards, including, but not limited to:
24 1. Structural integrity under expected loads;
Req. No. 13300 Page 1

1 2. Proper bedding and backfill placement;
2 3. Joint integrity and alignment; and
3 4. Absence of significant defects such as cracks, deformations,
4 or separations.
5 C. The contractor shall bear the cost of the post-installation
6 inspection and any corrective measures required to meet the
7 Departmentâ€™s standards. If a storm pipe fails the post-installation
8 inspection, the contractor shall take corrective action, which may
9 include removal and replacement, reinforcement, or other remediation
10 as directed by the Department.
11 D. The Oklahoma Department of Transportation shall promulgate
12 rules necessary to implement and enforce the provisions of this
13 section, including, but not limited to, specifications for
14 inspections, testing protocols, and qualifications for inspectors.
15 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
